ing: 1 (14 ounce) can artichoke hearts, drained and chopped
1/2 lemon, juiced, or more to taste
1/4 teaspoon chopped fresh mint, or to taste
1/4 teaspoon chopped fresh oregano, or to taste
1/4 teaspoon chopped fresh thyme, or to taste
des: "A fresh-tasting salad from ingredients that last a long time in the pantry and refrigerator, with a pleasing balance of earthy, sharp, salty, and green. Flat or Italian parsley has a much better flavor than curly, but either will do, and I've used a tablespoon of dried in a pinch."
ins: Combine chickpeas, artichokes, celery, feta cheese, parsley, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, mint, oregano, and thyme together in a bowl; toss to coat completely.
